$ X Window Manager
@ window manager

The → Linux/window-manager[window manager] is concerned with how (application-)windows look like and where they are created.
-
A window manager controls the placement and appearance of windows within a windowing system in a graphical user interface.


{ implementations

  Some window manager need a → Linux/X/desktop-environment, others, such as WindowMaker, sawfish, fvwm etc don't.

  Other implementations: → Linux/X/Openbox, metacity (practically unusable without GNOME), twm …

}

sa:
  → Linux/X#x-components[X components]

  → Linux/X/task-manager

  → Linux/shell/commands/wmctrl to interact with an EWMH/NetWM compatible window manager.
